The paper discusses a cloud-based architecture for secure management and analysis of social science data, which involves aspects of data security, database management, cybersecurity, information retrieval, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
